            <lg met="sragdharā" n="1">
                <l n="a"><lb n="1"/><g type="floretQuatrefoil"/> śrīmā<unclear>ñ ch</unclear>rī-dharmmasi<unclear>ṁh</unclear>aḥ prathi<unclear>ta</unclear>ta<unclear>ra</unclear>-yaśo dig-vidiś-cāpa-<unclear>ś</unclear>o<unclear>bhaḥ</unclear></l>
                <l n="b"><lb n="2"/>dharmmajñaḥ <unclear>Ā</unclear>dya-dāntaḥ <unclear>ri</unclear>pu-gaṇa-vijayaḥ śaktimān tyāga-śūraḥ <g type="danda"/></l>
                <l n="c"><lb n="3"/>trailokya<unclear>ṁl lo</unclear>kanārthaḥ <unclear>A</unclear>para-hi<unclear>ta-rata</unclear> sthāpitan tena śailaṁ</l>
	                    <!-- lokanārthaḥ = avalokanārthaḥ?
	                        comprendre rata = ratas, ou lire rataṁ? -->
                <l n="d"><lb n="4"/>mūrttiḥ-bāṇā<unclear>śva</unclear>-śā<unclear>ke</unclear> <seg met="------++-+"><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="10"/></seg> śukla-pakṣe</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus"/>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
         <p>L'illustre Śrī Dharmasiṁha est d'une renommée fort répandue, doté de la beauté de l'arc en ciel dans toutes les directions cardinales et intermédiaires; conscient du <foreign>dharma</foreign>; d'une retenue hors paire; conquérant des ennemis en masse; puissant; champion de générosité. Soucieux du bien des autres, pour surveiller (<foreign>lokana</foreign> = <foreign>avalokana</foreign>?) les Trois Mondes, il a érigé la pierre, dans la quinzaine claire ... <supplied reason="undefined">de l’année</supplied> śaka <supplied reason="undefined">exprimée comme</supplied> (8) formes, (5) flèches, (7) chevaux <supplied reason="explanation">donc en 758 śaka</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Irregularities of sandhi: <foreign>-jñaḥ Ādya-</foreign>, <foreign>mūrttiḥ-bā-</foreign>; stradding the cesura, sandhi is alternatively applied (a <foreign>-yaśo / dig-</foreign>), or not applied (b <foreign>-dāntaḥ / ripu-</foreign>, c <foreign>-nārthaḥ / Apara-</foreign>).</p>
         </div>
